<sect1 id="what-is-gnumeric">
  <title>What is Gnumeric?</title>
  <para>Welcome to Gnumeric, a well developed free software based spreadsheet. 
We hope you find Gnumeric intuitive and easy to use. This manual will guide 
you through using all the aspects of Gnumeric.</para>
  <para>Great qualities of Gnumeric include:</para>
  <itemizedlist>
  <listitem> <para>
  <guilabel>Fully featured.</guilabel> &mdash; Gnome has the full range of 
features expected in a quality spreadsheet application. These include 
support for graphs, an extensive range of functions, cell-formatting, printing, 
a plug-in system, internationalisation and much more!
  </para> </listitem>
  <listitem> <para>
  <guilabel>Compatibility with existing spreadsheet applications.</guilabel> 
&mdash; Gnome has a powerful range of import and export filters which will 
import your existing Excel, 1-2-3, Applix, Sylk, and other file formats.
  </para> </listitem>
  <listitem> <para>
  <guilabel>Graphs and component support.</guilabel> &mdash; Gnome uses 
the <keycap>Bonobo component architecture</keycap> to support drawing graphs 
and other components. 
  </para> </listitem>
  <listitem> <para>
  <guilabel>Free Software</guilabel> &mdash; Gnome is <ulink type="http" 
url="http://www.gnu.org/philosophy/free-sw.html">free software</ulink> 
released under the <ulink type="http" url="http://www.gnu.org/copyleft/gpl.html">GNU 
GPL</ulink>.
  </para> </listitem>
  <listitem> <para>
  <guilabel>Documentation</guilabel> &mdash; Gnome is fully documented with 
an extensive online manual and documentation covering all functions. 
  </para> </listitem>
  </itemizedlist> 
</sect1>
<sect1 id="spreadsheet">
  <title>What is a spreadsheet?</title>
  <para>A spreadsheet is an application that will help you manage any kind 
of data. It will allow you to store large amounts of data, process them 
according to varying formulae, and calculate results and graphs. It is 
especially good for data sets involving lots of numbers. Gnumeric has a 
huge range of functions which can process your figures.</para>
  <para>A spreadsheet can be used to maintain budget data, time allocations, 
personal finances, membership lists and more. Anything which involves storage 
and processing of number based data sets are good for handling in a spreadsheet.</para>
