<sect1>
  <title>Getting started.</title>
  <para>The best way to learn how to use Gnumeric is to begin exploring the 
program yourself. Type in some numbers into some cells and see what you can 
do to them. For writing formulae look at <xref linkend="formulas"> You might 
also be interested in learning how to format the data, so look at 
<xref linkend="cell-formatting"> </para>
  <para>If you would like further investigate functionality Gnumeric offers, 
browse through the table of contents to the <xref linkend="index">. You will 
be able to see what advanced features Gnumeric has. To see the very big list 
of functions that Gnumeric supports, look at <xref linkend="reference"></para>
  <para>If you would like a step by step tour through each part of the Gnumeric 
interface, then read the following chapter entitled 
<link linkend="worksheet">The Worksheet</link> It will take you through 
each element of the Gnumeric graphical user interface, explaining the purpose 
of each part.</para>
</sect1>


